catalog.title: Astronomy and Cosmic Origins
catalog.description: PHY 121 is a one-semester survey of astronomy. In PHY 121 we study the history of astronomy, the origin and structure of the Solar System, the stars and stellar evolution, neutron stars and black holes, cosmology, and life in the universe.

catalog.title: Computational Physics 2
catalog.description: More advanced physics problems involving partial differential equations. Numerical simulation and Monte Carlo methods, data analysis and fast Fourier transforms, use of mathematical library routines and computer algebra programs.
catalog.subject: Physics
catalog.requisites_description: Pre-Requisite: PHY 410.

catalog.title: Thermal & Stat Physics 2
catalog.description: Covers quantum statistics of ideal Bose and Fermi systems, applications to electrons in metals, blackbody radiation, Bose condensation, neutron stars, interacting systems, lattice vibrations, nonideal gases, ferromagnets, kinetic theory of transport processes, irreversible processes, and fluctuations.
catalog.subject: Physics

catalog.title: Nuclear & Particle Physics
catalog.description: Explores fundamentals of nuclear physics, including interaction of radiation with matter; properties of nuclear forces; nuclear structure described by shell and collective models; nuclear reactions; radioactive decay processes; and properties of elementary particles.
catalog.subject: Physics

catalog.title: Electronics
catalog.description: Introduction of DC and AC circuit design of analysis, Thevenin and Norton theorems, diodes and applications, properties and uses of BJT and FET transistors, negative feedback, properties and uses of operational amplifiers.
catalog.subject: Physics

notes.note: Pre-Reqs: PHY 207 or PHY 217; PHY 307, PHY 401

catalog.title: Advanced Physics Lab
catalog.description: Covers modern physics, with a choice of experiments: atomic physics, modern laser optics, solid state, magnetic resonance, X-ray diffraction, scanning probe microscopy, nuclear, or particle physics. Two four-hour labs each week.
catalog.subject: Physics
catalog.requisites_description: Pre-Requisite: PHY 307 and PHY 401.

catalog.title: Advanced Physics Lab
catalog.description: Covers modern physics, with a choice of experiments: atomic physics, modern laser optics, solid state, magnetic resonance, X-ray diffraction, scanning probe microscopy, nuclear, or particle physics. Two four-hour labs each week.
catalog.subject: Physics
catalog.requisites_description: Pre-Requisite: PHY 307 and PHY 401.

catalog.title: Electricity & Magnetism 2
catalog.description: Undertakes further study of Maxwell's equations, electric and magnetic susceptibilities, electromagnetic radiation, electromagnetic fields from a moving charge, waveguides and transmission lines, Poynting's vector, and Lorentz force. Also examines relativistic invariance.
catalog.subject: Physics
catalog.requisites_description: Pre-Requisite: PHY 403.

catalog.title: Quantum Mechanics II
catalog.description: Angular momentum, three-dimensional problems, hydrogen atom, time-independant perturbation theory, electron spin and fine structure, time-dependent perturbation theory, quantum statistics.
catalog.subject: Physics
catalog.requisites_description: Pre-Requisite: PHY 401.

catalog.title: Solid State Physics
catalog.subject: Physics
catalog.requisites_description: Pre-Requisite: PHY 401 and PHY 405.
